		<td><b>Laser Cut Wood NES Schematic</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've been working on making a new design for the NES schematic (One that I feel better shows the interconnections of the chips, and how the cartridge fits in the whole system)  I made this on my laser cutter, it's the second in a series of vintage computing/gaming I've started making and selling recently.  My previous one was on the Commodore 64.<br /><br />I got some help from lidnariq (who has been correcting/posting the updated NES schematic referenced by the wiki - as I kept finding mistakes and inconsistencies between what I could find online)<br /><br />If anyone is interested, I'm <a href="https://www.etsy.com/listing/601544813/laser-cut-wood-nes-schematic" class="postlink">selling the NES schematic on Etsy</a>, and I would love feedback or suggestions on what to make next!

		
